  "content": {
    "problemStatement": "Write a program to find the maximum number of elements in the first array which are strictly greater than the elements of the second array.\n\nNote: The element can be considered only once.\n\nFor Example:\n\nInput arrays: {20,30,50},{25,40,60}\n\nThe output is: 2\n\nExplanation:\n\nMaximum 2 elements 30(30 > 25) and 50(50>40) of array arr1 is greater than arr2.",
    "constraints": [
      "1 <= N <= 10^5",
      "1 <= arr[i] <= 10^5"
    ],
    "inputFormat": "First line has the size N.\n\nSecond and third line contains the array elements.\n\nThe given arrays are sorted.",
    "outputFormat": "Print the count of the elements which are greater than the elements of the second array.",
